    <div class="AssessmentProblem.identifier">102761</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.type">ShortAnswerResponse</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.statement"><p>To make purple paint, mix 2 cups of blue paint with 3 cups of red paint.</p>

<div class="imgrid">
<div class="g--row g--row-1">
<div class="g--column g--half g--content g--col-1 g--row-1">
<ol>
	<li>Complete the table showing the number of cups of blue and red paint that would make the same shade of purple.
	<table border="1">
		<thead>
			<tr>
				<th scope="col">blue paint (cups)</th>
				<th scope="col">red paint (cups)</th>
			</tr>
		</thead>
		<tbody>
			<tr>
				<th>2</th>
				<td>3</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<th>1</th>
				<td></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<th>7</th>
				<td></td>
			</tr>
		</tbody>
	</table>
	</li>
	<li>Draw a double number line that shows the same information.</li>
</ol>
</div>

<div class="g--column g--half g--content g--col-2 g--row-1">
<ol>
	<li>Which representation do you think works better in this situation? Explain why.</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.solution"><ol>
	<li>&#xA0;
	<table border="1">
		<thead>
			<tr>
				<th scope="col">blue paint (cups)</th>
				<th scope="col">red paint (cups)</th>
			</tr>
		</thead>
		<tbody>
			<tr>
				<th>2</th>
				<td>3</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<th>1</th>
				<td>
<span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="13863">\(\frac 32\)</span> (or equivalent)</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<th>7</th>
				<td>
<span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="47623">\(\frac {21}{2}\)</span>&#xA0;(or equivalent)</td>
			</tr>
		</tbody>
	</table>
	</li>
	<li>&#xA0;
	<p><img class="h-max-height--9-lines" src="/image_files/30691.png" /></p>
	</li>
	<li>Answers vary. Sample response: The table is more convenient, because the rows of the table can be listed in any order and with no need to worry about placing numbers accurately on the number line.</li>
</ol>
</div>
